Barely 24 hours that Kayode Fayemi, Ekiti state Governor-elect and Adam Oshiomole, national chairman of All Progressives Congress (APC) were sent by President Muhammadu Buhari to lead the party delegation to secure Iyiola Omisore’s support for APC in the Osun state governorship rerun poll, Boss Mustapha, Secretary to the Government of the Federation has also visited Social Democratic Party (SDP) governorship candidate on the same course. Recall that Omisore contested Osun governorship poll on the platform of Social Democratic Party (SDP) and came third after PDP governorship candidate, Ademola Adeleke and APC governorship candidate, Gboyega Oyetola for which INEC ordered rerun of the poll in seven units after declaring the poll inconclusive since the cancelled votes were far more than victory margin of 353 votes. Mustapha, who arrived at Iyiola Omisore’s country home residence in Ile-Ife few hours after he announced support for APC in the rerun election holding on Thursday, was received with cheers by many supporters of the ex-federal lawmaker. The SGF, who came in company of Ekiti state governor-elect, Kayode Fayemi, said he is a progressive leader, who deserves respect. He said: ” My wife is from Osun state. I am a stakeholder. Omisore is a national leader. He is just coming out of an election, so I decided to see him”. Reacting, Senator Omisore, welcomed Mustapha and promised to continue to work for the progress of the country.  BOLADALE BAMIGBOLA, Osogbo 